{
  "text": "Unfavorable karyotype together with thrombocytopenia were then identified as being the most important risk factors for leukemic evolution in PMF [CITATION_1] . The latter was reported in 6% and 12% of patients at 5 and 10 years, respectively, in the absence of any risk factor, whereas it was substantially higher in patients with one or more risk factors, i.e. 18% and 31% at 5 and 10 years, respectively [CITATION_2] . More recent studies have confirmed the adverse effect of specific cytogenetic abnormalities, with a 2-year rate of leukemic transformation of 29.4% in patients with a monosomal karyotype as compared with 8.3% if a complex karyotype was documented [CITATION_3] .",
